article.headline: Nevada 69, Idaho 61
article.story: RENO, Nev. (AP) -- Freshman Armon Johnson scored 23 points to lead Nevada over Idaho 69-61 in a Western Athletic Conference game on Thursday. Marcelus Kemp scored 18 points and JaVale McGee and Brandon Fields had 13 apiece for the Wolf Pack (10-6, 2-1 WAC). Jordan Brooks had 20 points and Michael Crowell 16 for the Vandals (4-12, 1-4 WAC), who stayed close throughout the second half. Nevada led by 9 points several times in the second half, the last at 56-47 with 6:52 to play on a pair of free throws by Fields. Clyde Johnson hit a pair of 3-point baskets around a free throw by McGee to pull the Vandals to within 4 at 57-53 with 5:28 left, but could get no closer. Armon Johnson hit 7 of 8 free throws down the stretch for the Wolf Pack. He was 10 of 12 from the line for the game. Nevada trailed 23-22 with 6:27 left in the first half, but went on a 13-5 run to lead 36-27 at halftime. The two teams combining for 46 fouls. Nevada hit 23 of 33 free throws, while Idaho hit only 10 of 22. The Wolf Pack dominated the boards, out-rebounding the Vandals 41-28. Demarshay Johnson had 11 rebounds, six of them offensive, for Nevada.
